project.name: Grid Domain
project.description: This domain was extracted from IPC-1 (1998) and was created by Jana Koehler, based on an earlier domain by Drew McDermott. There is a square grid of locations. A robot can move one grid square at a time horizontally and vertically. If a square is locked, the robot can move to it only by unlocking it, which requires having a key of the same shape as the lock. The goal is to get keys from various locations to various new locations.

operator.name: unlock
operator.description: unlock a place that is locked by using the right key.

useCase.name: Pickup a new key and loose the old key

action.precondition: robot.atRobot = curpos and curpos.conn->exists(p:Place|p = nextpos) and nextpos.open = true
robot.atRobot = curpos and curpos.conn->exists(p:Place| p = lockpos) and key.keyShape = shape and lockpos.lockShape = shape and lockpos.locked = true and robot.holding = key
robot.atRobot = curpos and key.at = curpos and robot.armEmpty = true
action.postcondition: robot.holding = key and key.at = null and robot.armEmpty = false

action.precondition: robot.atRobot = curpos and robot.holding = oldkey and newkey.at = curpos
action.postcondition: robot.holding = newkey and oldkey.at = curpos and newkey.at = null
robot.armEmpty = true and key.at = curpos and robot.holding = null
